  Shewhart and other pioneers in the field

DISCLAIMER:

This software is designed to assist with statistical process control and
quality management activities. While it implements FDA 21 CFR Part 11
compliance features, users are responsible for:

- Validating the system according to their specific regulatory requirements
- Ensuring proper installation, configuration, and maintenance
- Conducting appropriate validation studies and documentation
- Maintaining backup and disaster recovery procedures
- Training personnel on proper use of the system
- Conducting periodic system reviews and audits

The developers make no warranty regarding regulatory compliance or fitness
for any specific regulatory environment. Users in regulated industries should
consult with qualified validation specialists and regulatory experts to ensure
the system meets their specific compliance requirements.

DATA PRIVACY AND SECURITY:

This software may process sensitive manufacturing and quality data. Users are
responsible for:

- Implementing appropriate access controls and user authentication
- Ensuring data encryption in transit and at rest as required
- Maintaining audit trails according to regulatory requirements
- Implementing backup and disaster recovery procedures
- Complying with applicable data privacy regulations (GDPR, CCPA, etc.)
- Conducting security assessments and penetration testing as appropriate

